The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a eulogy for former President George H.W. Bush at the United States Capitol Rotunda. Pence expressed his deepest sympathies and respects to the Bush family and praised President Bush's lifetime of service and leadership. He highlighted Bush's military service in the Navy, his career in politics, and his achievements as Vice President and President. Pence also shared a personal story about receiving a letter from Bush for his son's military accomplishment. He emphasized Bush's kindness, modesty, and patriotism, and described him as a good man who loved his family and served his country. Pence concluded by expressing hope and offering prayers for comfort to those mourning Bush's loss.